annotation.TEXT: Huh, this pipe's two-way for some odd reason.
So, place your votes, and we'll find out where I'll go next time! To be continued...

Or, maybe I am done. I thought there was one more fishing fish guy up here, but maybe he failed to spawn for some reason. Well, anyway, this is how you safely grab this star coin, which should be the last one you collect.
Okay, the power up block has a flower instead of a feather...
And there's more than one of these guys, just to make my life more miserable. Man, is this power up over here even worth going for?
Goal tape average so far: 2704 / 69 = 39.188 stars each.
Alright, now it's time to look at those voting results. Let me just get back to my usual non-level spot in the center of the universe here...
Okay, I dodged it there. Now, do I want to try for that power up on the right again? ...Yeah.
Well, here's the P-switch you'd normally use to get past that brown block wall. I guess I'll use it to collect the 5 coins I missed.
I just had to check that pipe, didn't I? Now I'm no longer spin jumping, and I kind of want to be...
...I can get an extra P-switch! Just note that the one I carried through the pipe will now act like a blue P-switch.
Oh, man. Here we go with more of those fishing fish guys. Don't swim too high on this one here, or you'll get stuck in a dead end and be forced to backtrack and deal with this guy even more.
Darn it! That's okay. I know that there are cape feathers coming up shortly...
Yeah, I saw that huge combo opportunity there and went for it. And it was awesome!
We've got some tricky squeezes here. However, the lag seems to want to help me...
Yay, now this part of the Challenge Star world is no longer isolated from the rest of it! Alright, now let's go around and see which levels are available now...
Oh, man. I wonder if this'll be anything like the original SMW's Sunken Ghost Ship...
And, this is the reason I can travel through here...
Oh, geez. It's a miracle that I didn't die there, but I hope I don't get hit again...
Yeah, screw the P-switch. I need to be able to ascend fast.

Oh, it looks like the ON/OFF block did more than just toggle the switch blocks. I'm swimming here now (actually, I think this one particular pipe entrance is set to make this level an underwater level). Oh, and hey, this pipe is two-way, so...
Eh, screw checking every single pipe. If any of these pipes actually lead somewhere, let me know.
Okay, so I'm no longer swimming. Hmm... How am I supposed to get that star coin safely? (Well, I already know how, from watching raocow do this level.)
Goal tape average so far: 2744 / 70 = 39.2 stars each.
And, there's the goal. Strangely, I'm still swimming here for some reason. Is this screen supposed to be underwater? (Perhaps, given the theme of this world.)
Oh, since that P-switch acted like a blue one, it's turned these brown blocks into coins for me!

Nuts... That's okay. There's a replacement feather right there. Hmm... Maybe it isn't such a good idea to try swimming here with this extra P-switch. I'm sure the level wasn't specifically designed around me carrying something right now.
Looks like I can take a little breather here, but it also looks like an Eerie generator has been put into effect.
Make sure you're ready to glide immediately upon collecting that cape!
Oh, man. It's the fishing fish guy, and he's kind of in the way. This could be a pain...
Oh, man. So many munchers...
If you said, "3-1", then I don't know what kind of bologna you've been eatin', but it certainly wasn't of the Oscar Mayer variety...
Well, at least ducking under the guy can be surprisingly effective.
Yes! I'm surprised I pulled that off! But, I'm not quite done yet...
Ahhh! Nooo! I need my cape to survive in this harsh environment!
Yes, I'm playing 9-5, of course. I wonder how heavenly this will be...

Wind plus moving holes... That doesn't sound like a very good equation. I think we also need to multiply by ghosts as well. Ah, there we go. Next, let's subtract 404 computer hamsters and then divide the result by zero to get the result we really want.
Wow, I've got a bunch of Eeries grouped together there. Actually, that might be a good thing if I can keep that group on screen, to reduce the number of other Eeries that can show up.
WRECKER! (8 kills) 4-life, 23-coin combo!
Okay, now this part is definitely "OMGWTHIT!?"-worthy, but I've already planned out what I intend to do here. (Also, screw those other four ? blocks that I didn't hit. They're probably just coins.)
And, on top of that, going back through this pipe causes there to be a background glitch here. Umm... I think the initial BG position from this pipe entrance needs to be adjusted.
At least the background isn't glitched when coming out of that pipe. Hmm... There's a P-switch on the spikes down there. How would I ever get to it safely?
Oh, no. Another fishing fish guy?
Yes, I'd say that a second cape would be a good idea here.
Oh, forget it. I'm just gonna go on ahead in a ducking pose instead.

As a bonus, the first fishing fish guy here got turned into a silver coin that I can use to get a small discount on something at Big Y. Too bad the other fishing fish guys in this place will be unaffected, and this P-switch won't work on them, since it acts like a blue one now...
Yep, so it looks like I'm finally going to play a world 6 level!
That unlocks 6-2 (and cut out the map music, which is strange, since I didn't fight a boss at the end of 6-1). Now, 9-5 came in second in the voting, so guess where I'm headed next!
Argh! I clipped the side of that pipe, making the game think I landed for a split second, which halted my spinning!
Okay, how do I do this? ...Oh, that's how. That's kind of tricky.

Yeah, if you don't have a cape here, these currents can't completely support you and you'll gradually fall. However, cape gliding allows you to rise with these currents. Yeah, I guess this trivializes a lot of the difficulty here, unless you get hit...
No, it doesn't look like I can go over the top.
I wonder why I'm allowed to walk through here...
Whoa! Almost royally screwed up there! I need to do a spin jump and bounce off those Boos.
Ugh! How am I supposed to dodge that cheap flame?
Let's not loiter around in the Boo Cloud room unnecessarily.
D'oh! I thought I could get them all... How did I grab a coin in the middle there without grabbing the ones above or below it? Man, the SMW hit detection is weird.
And, there you go! Those are the 10 levels that you guys can vote for this time! (Hey, that's down from the 11 we've been at for a while!)
Oh, now I've gotta spin jump off of one of these guys? Well, actually, this isn't quite as bad as trying to dodge his flame below...
Oh, man. Wind. Who didn't see that coming? I think switching to the cape might be a good idea here.
Huh, what? I just noticed this. How come the player name in the upper-left corner still says "Luica"? Shouldn't it have switched back to "Marina"?
Yeah, these Challenge Star levels tend to make you earn your midpoints. This one is particularly tricky.
Argh... Should've waited a bit longer.
Whoa, whoa, whoa! What are you guys doing here already? In the original Sunken Ghost Ship, these phasing Boos don't appear until the second room!
Ow... I hate how erratically he moves and how his flame can just "teleport"...
Oh, I can totally get that 1P... Oh, come on!
D'oh! I was so close to escaping unscathed... Oh, that's interesting where I managed to land.
Good thing I know what my cape is capable of!
That's the last star coin. Oh, please don't tell me I have to deal with Torpedo Teds now!
This almost qualifies as "OMGWTHIT!?", but not quite. (Maybe it would if I didn't have a cape.)

And yes, I looked back to when I first discovered these player switch blocks, and this name glitch existed back then too. I just didn't notice it before. However, once I leave this area, the glitch ends and the correct name gets displayed.
Alright, a replacement cape, and it looks like I've gotta "A"...
Hmm... Can I cheat the system?
Why were those stupid Boos in the way? Well, I certainly wasn't going to sacrifice a hit to get a worthless item, since I'm already at 99 lives.

Hey there, everyone! Welcome back to Super Marina World! Now, before I get to the voting results, I think I'm going to have Luica pass the turn back to Marina here. (I'll probably make future switches off screen.)

Note that I've got some silly votes up there sharing the same lines as other silly votes (for instance, bomboloni and Cookie Clicker are on the same line), just so I'd have more room to place annotations down here.
Actually, it does appear to have begun in a similar way to the original Sunken Ghost Ship...
5-life combo! Yeah, I'm not star-killing anything else, and I'm waiting for it to expire so that I can bounce off a Boo below and enter the pipe.
Alright, I can definitely use this spare cape.
Well, no Torpedo Teds appeared, and there was a smiley in the coins, but... Oh, geez...
BGM: Touhou 12 - Kogasa's Theme - Beware the Umbrella Left There Forever
Okay, I managed to pull of a frame-perfect spin jump there...
Here we are at midpoint, and there's an ON/OFF block that we should've been expecting all this time, since we've seen so many of those green switch blocks along the way.
